        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 1:11PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 111 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Mclean, or 19 miles west of Shamrock, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mclean.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 141 and 152.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
